adjectives.description: unaware (comparative more unaware, superlative most unaware)

entries.meaning: Not aware or informed; lacking knowledge.
examples: I'm unaware of the answer to that question.
Luckily, she was unaware that I'd spent the last five years in prison.

entries.meaning: Not noticing; paying no heed; thoughtless; inattentive.
examples: Or on the mat devoutly kneeling,Would lift her eyes up to the ceiling,And heave her bosom unawareFor neighbouring beaux to see it bare.
